<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
	<h2>CLUB RIDES & EVENTS</h2>

	<h3>Come and join in!</h3>

	<p>
		Rides are provided for Club Members every Sunday. Check the Events page
		for more info. Club events include a full Time Trial Club Events
		calendar throughout the spring and summer, two Audax events in May and
		various informal social rides throughout the year. We organise an annual
		Open 25 Time Trial event. This is held at the end of August and club
		members can ride for free. RDFCC also assist and advise on the Wild Boar
		Chase which is organised by the Forest of Dean Lions Club. and this year
		will be held in September.
	</p>

	<a href="../joinus/">Join Us!</a>

	<h2>CLUB RIDES & EVENTS</h2>

	<h3>You're covered!</h3>

	<p>
		The RDFCC are affiliated with a number of national cycling organisations
		who provide a range of basic insurance cover when participating in club
		events and rides. For further details please visit: British Cycling
		Cycling Time Trials Cycling UK ​ RDFCC affiliation with Cycling Time
		Trials provides riders with basic insurance at RDFCC club time trials
		(it is not possible to ride our club time trials without being a member
		of the RDFCC or another affiliated club). RDFCC membership will also
		allow you to ride the club time trials of other clubs who are also
		affiliated (e.g. Ross & District CC and Newport Phoenix), as well as
		Open CTT events.
	</p>

	<h2>DISCOUNTED CLUB KIT</h2>

	<h3>Let's kit you out!</h3>

	<p>
		RDFCC currently purchase club kit from Champion System UK. The kit is
		discounted by the club in special offers when the 'club shop' is opened.
		See Ali Colquoun for more details. Club kits promote the club on rides
		and at events.
	</p>

